title: For Sale:  Complete Custom Gen 3 Glock 17 frame
postcontent:
This is a highly customized Gen 3 Glock 17 frame. It is ready to go, just needs a top end and a magazine! 
Here are a breakdown of the customizations1.) Glock "hump" reduction
This process removes the extreme "hump" that is most often the point of complaint with Glock handguns. If you prefer the point-ability of a 1911 grip angle but the mechanical platform of a Glock, you will LOVE this frame. Many users find that Glocks tend to point up on a draw because of the angle created by the hump. That issue has been solved on this frame.
2.) Recessed Borders Stipple job
This is the newest evolution in grip modification. It is a time consuming and delicate process, but the results are far more impressive than the standard "melted dot" stipple job most are used to seeing. This particular stipple job uses a combination of two stipple-specific tip patterns (OTD X-tip and Wagon Wheel) that creates a uniform-but-random pattern while maintaining a clean, sharp edge around the borders. This texture is aggressive enough to prevent slippage when hands are sweaty or in raining conditions without being at all uncomfortable in the hand. It feels great, and looks great, too.
3.) Finger Groove Removal
This is another major complaint with Gen 3 Glocks as many people find the finger grooves do not line up with their fingers in a tight grip. I have taken off the bottom two grooves to allow the end user to place their fingers wherever they naturally fall, utilizing the superior texture for grip rather than the shape of the frame. I have left the top-half of the 1st finger groove in place (explained below)
4.) Polished half finger groove
As mentioned above, I left the top-half of the 1st finger groove in place but I have polished it to a smooth finish. Coupled with the double undercut (explained below) this allows for a high, comfortable and locked-in grip, helping to prevent muzzle rise and grip slip when firing.
5.) Double undercut
The double undercut removes material from underneath the trigger guard in the two places where your firing-hand middle finger and your off-hand pointer finger make contact with the frame. This allows the user to get a higher grip on the frame in relation to the bore axis, helping to control muzzle rise/recoil when firing. The entire section has been polished smooth for comfort. If you've never held a Glock with a double undercut incorporating the polished half-finger groove, you need to. It changes everything!
6.) Trigger guard de-horn
This customization is primarily aesthetic, tying in the lines created with the undercut and half-finger groove with the rest of the frame. It does have some practical application as it makes the gun less likely to snag on clothing or gear upon reholstering.
7.) Accelerator cuts
This customization removes material forward of the take-down lever, moving upward at a 45-degree angle. This accomplishes three distinctly different improvements. Firstly, it makes getting a grip on the take-down lever easier, aiding in the breakdown of the weapon for maintenance. Secondly, it creates a ledge where the shooter's off-hand thumb can create downward leverage with a "thumbs forward" grip, reducing muzzle flip. On the shooting-hand side, it provides a tactile ledge for the shooter's trigger finger to rest while not firing in the "straight-and-off-the-trigger" position.
8.) Eliminated Lanyard Hole
Another complaint about Gen 3 Glocks is the lanyard hole that no one uses. I have filled this in on the frame to clean up the look.
9.) Polished slide lock/release
 This customization is also aesthetic, tying the color of the lock/release with the LoneWolf Ultimate Adjustable Trigger kit (explained below).
10.) LoneWolf Distributing Ultimate Adjustable Trigger Kit
 This fully adjustable trigger features a 6061 Billet Aluminum shoe, smooth, symmetrical shape with large radiused edges, in-gun adjustability (no need to remove to adjust pre and over travel), 2 piece design allow easy trigger bar swap, finer adjustments compared to other adjustable trigger kits, over-sized safety spring allows more comfort to the shooters finger, safety lever is flush to the shoe for more comfort, no press out pins like the competition, one screw assembly, and tighter tolerances to lessen wobble between shoe and trigger bar. It is a great trigger and has been pre-adjusted for the best balance between pretravel and overtravel.
 
This frame would be perfect to start a custom build using a built/purchased slide assembly or to take your current Gen 3 G17 to the next level!
Email me and let's work it out! I don't mind shipping to your FFL if you cover fees/shipping chargesI have included two pictures of the frame with a slide installed so you can see what a completed project might look like with a stock slide assembly and a fully custom job. (Only the completed frame is for sale)
